bzip2 (1.0.8-5.1build0.1+safelibs1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Build staged Debian packages from the safe Rust libbz2 implementation.
  * Reuse the upstream CLI, documentation, and autopkgtest assets against the
    installed safe packages.
  * Refresh the package harness and downstream smoke tests to consume the
    generated .deb artifacts under target/package/out.
  * Keep the staged Debian build compatible with Ubuntu 24.04's Rust toolchain
    while preserving the drop-in SONAME and package split.
  * Stage only checked-in packaging sources into target/package/src so host
    cargo build output does not leak into the Debian source tree.

